2305761,0.06811388,0.04014714,0.06493180,0.00190794,-0.00858903,-0.02888160,0.06372032,0.05543928,0.01175004,0.16485402,-0.01055995,-0.01598062,-0.03488972,0.00883906,0.01922008,0.01440099,-0.04181832,-0.06247550,0.02481090,-0.04519181,0.02850048,0.07610431,0.00388005,-0.03589452,-0.03702610,0.00530388,0.00199550,-0.02677295,0.00948619,0.02416518,0.01040679,-0.00807344,-0.03760718,0.01289429,-0.02143079,-0.05484699,-0.00117074,0.03677420,0.01977573,-0.00190936,0.04125069,0.00383466]',E'List\n\nAs we see above, the Non-Null and List modifiers can be combined. For example, you can have a List of Non-Null `String` types:\n\n{/* <!-- snippet-ignore --> */}\n```graphql\nmyField: [String!]\n```\n\nThis means that the _list itself_ can be null, but it can''t have any null members. For example, in JSON:\n\n```js\nmyField: null // valid\nmyField: [] // valid\nmyField: ["a", "b"] // valid\nmyField: ["a", null, "b"] // error\n```\n\nNow, let''s say we defined a Non-Null List of `String` types:','{"source": "graphql", "version": "1.0", "language": "graphql", "title": "Schemas and Types", "section_title": "schemax", "url": "https://github.com/graphql/graphql.github.io/blob/source/src/pages/learn/schema.mdx", "topics": "graphql,schemax", "categories": "api,query,graphql"}');
