89,0.19401230,0.00247732,0.01063355,-0.04888158,0.00851793,-0.03820046,0.03550671,0.03981347,0.01917468,-0.03000579,0.04759849,-0.02023195,0.00938848,-0.00016788,-0.06393398,0.01272229,-0.00908635,0.01909897,-0.06464770,-0.01158376,-0.02679904,0.05768041,0.06190104,0.02419057,0.01168786,-0.03122113,0.01953465,0.08683374,-0.03510030,-0.03721370,-0.02314945,0.00179335,0.07768547,0.05004930,-0.03222866,-0.01962665,0.03947038,0.11000367,0.00793706,-0.02720663,0.04929721,-0.01348354,0.00226751]',E'Pagination and edges\n\nThere are several ways we could do pagination:\n\n- We could do something like `friends(first:2 offset:2)` to ask for the next two in the list.\n- We could do something like `friends(first:2 after:$friendId)`, to ask for the next two after the last friend we fetched.\n- We could do something like `friends(first:2 after:$friendCursor)`, where we get a cursor from the last item and use that to paginate.','{"source": "graphql", "version": "1.0", "language": "graphql", "title": "Pagination", "section_title": "paginationx", "url": "https://github.com/graphql/graphql.github.io/blob/source/src/pages/learn/pagination.mdx", "topics": "graphql,paginationx", "categories": "api,query,graphql"}');
